comments.body: @michael_jacobi, I changed it now, it was not really handy when I uploaded these observations via the naturalist app.

@gjverspui Yes, the iNat app has its limitations and frustrates me often. I understand. I've taken to only using it for quick snapshots of dead snakes in the field. Everything else I do via the browser version later when I have time, with GPS coordinates recorded using the Gaia GPS app.
If you have an exact location, better to obscure for the general public but provide correct locality for researchers.
